doc.after: In 2011, 50 murders were reported, which is 6.1 per 100,000 people.[225] There were about 134 rapes, 3,142 robberies, and about 2,139 assaults. There were about 4,469 burglaries, 25,100 thefts, and 4,210 motor vehicle thefts.[226] The Tenderloin area has the highest crime rate in San Francisco: 70% of the city's violent crimes, and around one-fourth of the city's murders, occur in this neighborhood. The Tenderloin also sees high rates of homelessness, drug abuse, gang violence, and prostitution.[227] Another area with high crime rates is the Bayview-Hunters Point area. Homelessness is also a growing problem in the city.[228]
